23:02.881 --> 23:06.418 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's now a student at the John
Jay College
of Criminal Justice in New York.

23:06.452 --> 23:09.755 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But her path forward could get
much tougher.

23:09.788 --> 23:16.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Chacon is a recipient of DACA,
Deferred Action
for Childhood Arrivals, an Obama
administration

23:16.428 --> 23:21.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
policy that allows undocumented
immigrants
who entered the country as
children to work

23:21.734 --> 23:24.270 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and study here legally on a
temporary basis.

23:24.303 --> 23:27.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
If there is a young person here
who has grown

23:27.039 --> 23:35.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
up here and wants to contribute
to this society,
wants to maybe start a business
that will

23:35.114 --> 23:41.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
create jobs for other folks who
are looking
for work, that's the right thing
to do.

23:41.720 --> 23:44.189 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DIANA CHACON: DACA changed my
life.

23:44.223 --> 23:49.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It allowed me to be involved in
school more,
spend more time doing my class
work assignments,

23:49.995 --> 23:56.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
spend more time applying for
programs, and
just get involved in my
community in general.

23:56.702 --> 23:59.838 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I stopped making excuses for who
I was and
what position I was in.

23:59.872 --> 24:01.874 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I was so encouraged to keep
going.

24:01.907 --> 24:03.876 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I was encouraged to pursue law
school.

24:03.909 --> 24:09.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I knew that all the things I
have been doing
to this point were projecting me
into a better

24:09.782 --> 24:12.551 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
future, into a better life.

24:12.584 --> 24:18.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And all of that's going to
change because,
you know, now Donald Trump is
president.

24:18.257 --> 24:20.659 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
BARACK OBAMA: This is a
temporary stopgap
measure.

24:20.693 --> 24:25.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Unable to get
immigration legislation
passed, President Obama used his
executive

24:25.964 --> 24:27.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
power to create DACA.

24:27.733 --> 24:34.673 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, just as easily, it could be
undone, with
enormous potential consequences
for Chacon

24:34.707 --> 24:37.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the 800,000 other recipients
known as
dreamers.

24:37.976 --> 24:42.281 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP (R),
President-Elect: Anyone
who has entered the United
States illegally

24:42.314 --> 24:46.285 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is subject to deportation.

24:46.318 --> 24:49.922 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is what it means to have
laws and to
have a country.

24:49.955 --> 24:55.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: In addition to
building a wall,
Donald Trump as a candidate made
the repeal

24:55.294 --> 24:57.463 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of DACA a top priority.

24:57.496 --> 25:05.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And since the election, dreamers
and other
immigrants have protested across
the country.

25:05.170 --> 25:10.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Teresa Galindo, who brought her
two sons to
the U.S. from Mexico after her
husband's death,

25:10.442 --> 25:13.512 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
marched at a Sunday Midtown
Manhattan rally.

25:13.545 --> 25:18.550 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Her youngest, Carlos, now 31,
was just 2 years
old when he entered the country.

25:18.584 --> 25:23.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TERESA GALINDO, Undocumented
Mother (through
translator): It wasn't their
fault and it's

25:23.756 --> 25:25.023 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
still not their fault.

25:25.057 --> 25:27.493 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're here because I brought
them when they
were very young.

25:27.526 --> 25:29.828 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I did it as a mother to give my
kids the best.

25:29.862 --> 25:32.598 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I wanted to, and I still want to
give them
the best.

25:32.631 --> 25:35.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Back in my country, they
couldn't even get
an education.

25:35.134 --> 25:41.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Carlos got his
education, and
four years ago became a DACA
recipient.

25:41.039 --> 25:46.011 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He now works at an immigrants
rights organization
in Staten Island helping others
find legal

25:46.044 --> 25:47.880 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
