person, you're basically
deporting everybody

28:27.105 --> 28:30.842 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
else with that person, not
physically, but
emotionally.

28:30.876 --> 28:35.080 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Like, it's that baggage that's
left behind.

28:35.113 --> 28:37.616 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's not just me, just not you.

28:37.649 --> 28:40.352 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's everybody who is going to
be affected
indirectly.

28:40.385 --> 28:47.693 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And separating families,
separating friendships,
separating communities, in my
eyes, it's a

28:47.726 --> 28:48.961 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
form of violence.

28:48.994 --> 28:52.164 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: For now, she
remains focused
on her future.

28:52.197 --> 28:57.169 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DIANA CHACON: I don't want to
think that because
my life is in somebody else's
hands at the

28:57.202 --> 29:00.606 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
moment means that I don't have
control over
it anymore.

29:00.639 --> 29:06.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I am so much more than the
narratives that
are out there about me, about my
community.

29:06.845 --> 29:09.314 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You know that's something you
can't control.

29:09.348 --> 29:13.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what I can control is how
I'm going to
go about it and how I'm going to
take the

29:13.819 --> 29:15.287 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
few next steps.

29:15.320 --> 29:17.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm not going to let one piece
of paper define
me.

29:17.489 --> 29:19.858 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm not going to let a president
define me.

29:19.891 --> 29:21.927 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
I can't.

29:21.960 --> 29:26.865 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: From New York,
I'm Jeffrey
Brown for the "PBS NewsHour."

29:26.898 --> 29:40.746 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And now to the
analysis of
Brooks and Marcus.

29:40.779 --> 29:45.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's New York Times columnist
David Brooks
and Washington Post columnist
Ruth Marcus.

29:45.651 --> 29:46.718 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Mark Shields is away.

29:46.752 --> 29:49.354 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And happy Friday to both of you.

29:49.388 --> 29:55.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, president-elect Trump,
David, making these
three big announcements today in
the national

29:55.727 --> 29:58.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
security arena, after we heard
who a couple
of people are going to be around
him in the

29:58.864 --> 30:00.198 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
White House.

30:00.232 --> 30:02.401 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
What do we make of these
choices, starting
with the ones today?

30:02.434 --> 30:04.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Well, if you
thought Donald
Trump was going to be swallowed
up by the

30:04.936 --> 30:08.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
conventional Republican Party or
by Washington,
you were wrong.

30:08.774 --> 30:11.877 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's governing exactly, it
seems, as he campaigned.

30:11.910 --> 30:15.380 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the people he selected are
very much in
the spirit of the campaign,
sometimes explicitly

30:15.414 --> 30:17.616 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
referencing the policies he took
on the campaign.

30:17.649 --> 30:20.919 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I would say, A, they are
going to be very
different.

30:20.952 --> 30:24.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're going to have a very
different administration
from a normal Republican
administration, let

30:24.589 --> 30:26.024 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
alone a Democratic
administration.

30:26.058 --> 30:30.095 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Second, I have to say, they have
good resumes.

30:30.128 --> 30:35.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Pompeo, Flynn, they are -- it's
not like they're
just out of the wilderness.

30:35.967 --> 30:40.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These are people who have been
around power
and who probably are not going
to be automatically

30:40.872 --> 30:42.741 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
incompetent at their jobs.

30:42.774 --> 30:46.778 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The third thing to that we say
is, they have
Donald Trump's charm, which is
to say they

30:46.812 --> 30:51.049 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are extremely sharp-elbowed
individuals, to
a person.

30:51.083 --> 30:55.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's like he's taken all the
hard bosses
or bad bosses in the world and
so far he is

30:55.287 --> 30:56.988 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
bringing them all together.

30:57.022 --> 31:00.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, if they work as a team,
maybe they
will be a very tough team, but
they could

31:00.592 --> 31:02.627 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
work on each other.

31:02.661 --> 31:07.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it could be hard to hire
people under
them, because these are people
famous for

31:07.065 --> 31:09.768 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
being really hard on those
around them.

31:09.801 --> 31:12.571 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Ruth, what do you
make of these
national security picks?

31:12.604 --> 31:21.313 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH MARCUS: Disturbing on
General Flynn,
and less disturbing on
Congressman Pompeo.

31:21.346 --> 31:25.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it's really important
for us to understand
Donald Trump is the
president-elect, and he

31:25.350 --> 31:30.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is really entitled to -- he has
got the prerogative
to pick people who will
implement his policies

31:30.922 --> 31:33.158 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and who have his confidence.

31:33.191 --> 31:37.028 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I think -- I don't look at
it just as
the national security team.

31:37.062 --> 31:42.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I look at it as a whole, and I'm
very worried
that he is picking people -- he
talked on

31:42.267 --> 31:45.537 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
election night about the need to
bind the
wounds of division.

31:45.570 --> 31:49.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think he's picking a series of
people who
are potentially pouring salt
into the wounds

31:49.975 --> 31:55.414 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of division and who are
reinforcing some of
his worst tendencies, rather
than buttressing

31:55.447 --> 32:01.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
him and surrounding himself with
people who
bring to the table both
personality and capabilities

32:01.419 --> 32:04.122 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that he may be lacking in.

32:04.156 --> 32:10.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so I would -- the three that
most concern
me are General Flynn, Senator
Sessions, and

32:10.862 --> 32:13.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Steve Bannon at his right hand
in the White
House.

32:13.165 --> 32:14.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Who comes from
Breitbart News.

32:15.000 --> 32:16.668 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
RUTH MARCUS: Indeed.

32:16.701 --> 32:19.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Which raises -- I
saw some
commentary, David, saying, well,
maybe there

32:19.838 --> 32:24.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is good cop/bad cop thing going
on here in
the White House, where Donald
Trump picks

32:24.442 --> 32:28.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Reince Priebus, the chairman of
the Republican
Party, as his chief of staff,
but then he

32:28.914 --> 32:31.149 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
picks Bannon, Steve Bannon, to
be his counselor.

32:31.183 --> 32:34.352 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes, I'm not yet
putting Priebus
in my good cop category...

32:34.386 --> 32:35.353 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

32:35.387 --> 32:36.354 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

32:36.388 --> 32:37.622 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: ... bad and other
cops.

32:37.656 --> 32:39.391 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Bannon is the interesting case.

32:39.424 --> 32:43.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He is, of course -- I do not
approve of his
news organization or his
judgments, but he

32:44.029 --> 32:49.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is something out of a different
-- he is a
pure populist, pure
anti-establishment.

32:49.301 --> 32:52.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, for example, there was
an article
today, a rare interview that he
gave, where

32:52.838 --> 32:57.275 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he really talked about having a
trillion-dollar
infrastructure program.

32:57.309 --> 33:00.378 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That would be a big shift in our
national
debate.

33:00.412 --> 33:02.414 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think it might be a good
idea.

33:02.447 --> 33:04.316 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But it would get a lot of
Democrats on board.

33:04.349 --> 33:08.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I do think the silver lining
for those
of you who didn't approve of
Donald Trump

33:08.987 --> 33:14.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is that there are a lot of
policies in his
canon that do mess with our
categories.

33:14.092 --> 33:17.395 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that kind of big spending
program would
be one of them.

33:17.429 --> 33:19.197 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What do you
think?

33:19.231 --> 33:23.235 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH MARCUS: I'm kind of having
a hard time
seeing the Steve Bannon silver
lining here,

33:23.268 --> 33:30.709 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
even with a big infrastructure
program, because
his Web site and his own history
has been

33:30.742 --> 33:38.950 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so divisive, so hurtful to
people of -- minorities,
people of other faiths.

33:38.984 --> 33:45.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think having somebody like
that in the White
House -- I understand, to the
victor go the

33:45.123 --> 33:49.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
spoils, but bringing someone
like that inside
the White House who you're going
to be listening

33:49.160 --> 33:50.929 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to is a bad thing.

33:50.962 --> 33:55.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then we're layering on to
that I think
two people who are the wrong
people in the

33:55.934 --> 33:57.702 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
wrong jobs.

33:57.736 --> 34:00.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You want somebody who is going
to be your
national security adviser who is
going to

34:00.805 --> 34:04.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be temperate, who is going to be
an honest
broker, who is going to be able
to take in

34:04.209 --> 34:08.914 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
information and give you sort
of, this is
what everybody is saying.

34:08.947 --> 34:13.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That is not, from the people
that I have spoken
to today, what General Flynn is
all about.

34:13.418 --> 34:15.153 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: No.

34:15.186 --> 34:19.791 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH MARCUS: And, similarly,
with Senator
Sessions, I was around for his
confirmation

34:19.824 --> 34:20.792 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
hearings as judge.

34:20.825 --> 34:21.793 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: No.

34:21.826 --> 34:23.395 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RUTH MARCUS: Both in those -- I
know.

34:23.428 --> 34:24.896 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I look so young.

34:24.930 --> 34:25.897 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

34:25.931 --> 34:27.732 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RUTH MARCUS: But it's true.

34:27.766 --> 34:32.804 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Both in those and in his
performance as senator,
taking -- going to the Justice
Department,

34:32.837 --> 34:34.239 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
sort of same idea.

34:34.272 --> 34:38.209 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If he were up for secretary of
defense, I
might not have this issue.

34:38.243 --> 34:43.214 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we're at a country that is
facing enormous
racial tensions, really
difficult questions

34:43.248 --> 34:48.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about criminal justice reform
and tensions
between minority communities and
police, and

34:48.119 --> 34:50.221 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
here he is with a long history.

34:50.255 --> 34:51.589 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Wrong person, wrong job.

34:51.623 --> 34:52.924 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How much of a
worry is that,
David?

34:52.958 --> 34:55.627 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: I do think it is a
significant
worry.

34:55.660 --> 35:00.365 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, this past few weeks,
past few months,
past few years, maybe past few
centuries,

35:00.398 --> 35:03.368 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
have been rife with racial
tension.

35:03.401 --> 35:07.372 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this seems set to exploit
that and to
exacerbate that.

35:07.405 --> 35:12.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that's going to be one
of the most
likely and one of the ugliest
features of

35:12.043 --> 35:13.645 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the campaign.

35:13.678 --> 35:16.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm trying -- as I said on the
program last
week, I'm trying to give a
pause.

35:16.214 --> 35:17.682 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
The guy was elected.

35:17.716 --> 35:22.721 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And, as I say, he's been
extremely consistent
with his electoral campaign.

35:22.754 --> 35:26.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's being authentic to what he
ran on and
what got elected.

35:26.124 --> 35:27.092 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And so I agree with Ruth.

35:27.125 --> 35:29.060 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think these people deserve to
be confirmed.

35:29.094 --> 35:32.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's nobody who, I don't
think, doesn't
deserve to be confirmed.

35:32.364 --> 35:34.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One other point, though, and
this is about
the Bannon point.

35:34.866 --> 35:37.669 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's always had a teeny-tiny
circle of trust.

35:37.702 --> 35:41.606 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I can't imagine that being in
the Trump Cabinet
will be a very important job.

35:41.640 --> 35:45.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I do think this will be a White
House-run
administration with a teeny-tiny
group of

35:45.543 --> 35:47.912 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
people surrounding him,
including his family
maybe.

35:47.946 --> 35:51.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, and that's
-- I want
to ask about that, because one
thing everybody

35:51.783 --> 35:57.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
noticed is that his family is on
the transition
team, his children, his
son-in-law, Ruth.

35:57.922 --> 36:02.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They were -- his daughter Ivanka
and her husband,
Jared Kushner, were in that
meeting yesterday

36:02.494 --> 36:05.697 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
with the Japanese prime
minister.

36:05.730 --> 36:07.732 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Is this something -- I mean,
what?

36:07.766 --> 36:09.167 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What are we to make of this?

36:09.200 --> 36:11.636 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RUTH MARCUS: Well, again, quite
disturbing.

36:11.669 --> 36:16.508 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I do not begrudge anybody
relying on their
family members for advice.

36:16.541 --> 36:17.776 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
I do.

36:17.809 --> 36:20.979 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Politicians regularly rely on
family members
for advice.

36:21.012 --> 36:24.249 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But Donald Trump is in a unique
position here.

36:24.282 --> 36:28.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First of all, he has told us
that he is going
to solve -- and I don't think
it's a good

36:28.486 --> 36:33.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
solution -- his problems of
conflict of interests
in his business by turning over
the management

36:33.358 --> 36:34.459 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to his children.

36:34.492 --> 36:37.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
OK, maybe that's adequate from
his point of
view.

36:37.595 --> 36:41.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But now he's simultaneously
turning over the
management to his children and
bringing in

36:41.800 --> 36:47.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
his children, first three of
them, to the
transition, and then apparently
tapping his

36:47.572 --> 36:51.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
son-in-law, married to one of
the people who's
going to be managing this
business and dealing

36:51.509 --> 36:55.046 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with the conflict that way, to
bring them
into the White House.

36:55.080 --> 36:56.848 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's number one.

36:56.881 --> 37:01.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Number two, in this small
circle, you want
a president without governing
experience to

37:01.286 --> 37:04.222 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be surrounded by people with
experience in
governing.

37:04.255 --> 37:06.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Instead, it's insular Trump
surrounded by
his family.

37:07.025 --> 37:08.693 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Does that bother
you?

37:08.726 --> 37:12.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Well, what does
bother me is
the intermingling of the
business and the

37:12.230 --> 37:14.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
public service aspect of this.

37:14.799 --> 37:16.634 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And so I do agree with that.

37:16.668 --> 37:20.805 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I do think, if the family
members choose
one side or the other, I would
have no problem

37:20.839 --> 37:23.208 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with Ivanka serving on the White
House staff,
frankly.

37:23.241 --> 37:27.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there's a rule against it
now, in theory,
serving in the Cabinet, at
least, maybe not

37:27.078 --> 37:29.547 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the White House, that was
passed after
Bobby Kennedy.

37:29.581 --> 37:31.382 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I personally think that's a dumb
rule.

37:31.416 --> 37:35.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If a president wants to have a
family member
as -- an executive of a small
business can

37:35.386 --> 37:36.488 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
have a family member.

37:36.521 --> 37:37.922 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't have a problem with
that.

37:37.956 --> 37:41.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I actually think Ivanka would be
a good influence
on the administration.

37:41.726 --> 37:44.762 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I do think as long as the --
he's so business-minded.

37:44.796 --> 37:49.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As long as we're constantly
asking, is he
trying to make a buck off this,
is he trying

37:49.334 --> 37:54.205 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to promote his hotel with this,
then that's
just a corruption of what we
think of as public

37:54.239 --> 37:55.173 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
service.

37:55.206 --> 37:57.142 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

37:57.175 --> 37:59.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, I wanted to ask you both
about the Democrats
and where they stand right now,
back on their

37:59.644 --> 38:01.379 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
heels.

38:01.412 --> 38:03.982 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I really want to leave time
here at the
end for a few minutes to ask you
both about

38:04.015 --> 38:05.150 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our friend.

38:05.183 --> 38:07.318 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You both knew her well, Gwen.

38:07.352 --> 38:08.853 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
David, you were close friends.

38:08.887 --> 38:11.389 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ruth, you have worked with her
for so long.

38:11.422 --> 38:15.260 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ruth, you go back to, what,
early days at
The Washington Post.

38:15.293 --> 38:18.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH MARCUS: So, I can tell you
the exact
day, because it was my first day
at The Washington

38:18.396 --> 38:21.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Post, September 4, 1984.

38:21.199 --> 38:25.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I drove out to Prince George's
County, Upper
Marlboro, Maryland, walked into
the bureau,

38:25.803 --> 38:31.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and there was Gwen Ifill with
this luminous
smile that David wrote so
beautifully about.

38:31.643 --> 38:34.312 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we have been friends ever
since.

38:34.345 --> 38:38.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think -- thinking, she went to
The New York
Times, so we covered the White
House together.

38:38.950 --> 38:45.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I'm particularly remembering
one Christmas
Eve in Little Rock in 1992 after
the Clinton

38:45.924 --> 38:47.859 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
election.

38:47.892 --> 38:51.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think Gwen's editor had sent
her a bottle
of champagne, which we had to
drink surreptitiously

38:51.963 --> 38:54.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
out of teacups, because I think
the restaurant
was dry.

38:54.832 --> 38:56.601 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

38:56.634 --> 39:00.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH MARCUS: And then I have to
say finally
that it's actually thanks to
Gwen that I'm

39:00.171 --> 39:03.408 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sitting here tonight, because
Mark was going
to be away one day.

39:03.441 --> 39:08.079 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Jim said, "Hey, who can --
how can we
broaden the circle and bring
people in?"

39:08.112 --> 39:10.515 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Gwen said, "What about
Ruth?"

39:10.548 --> 39:17.855 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I know I'm not only person
for whom she
went to bat and said, why don't
we expand

39:17.889 --> 39:19.757 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the field of people that we use?

39:19.791 --> 39:22.260 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, so, I will miss her, and
I'm thankful
to her.

39:22.293 --> 39:24.095 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, she had an
eye for talent.

39:24.128 --> 39:25.797 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And we're glad you're here, too.

39:25.830 --> 39:27.498 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, David, she was so fond of
you.

39:27.532 --> 39:30.602 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes, and, well, I
wrote this
column.

39:30.635 --> 39:34.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the way I ended it, which I
think is a
point that is a true one, is
that nobody reminded

39:34.606 --> 39:35.907 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you of her.

39:35.940 --> 39:38.109 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You never thought, oh, who's
kind of like
Gwen?

39:38.142 --> 39:39.344 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Who's the next best Gwen?

39:39.377 --> 39:41.379 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There is no next best Gwen.

39:41.412 --> 39:46.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think what was unique
about her was
this combination of intense
strength with

39:46.951 --> 39:48.720 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
intense warmth.

39:48.753 --> 39:53.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, you know, one of the
toughest hours of
TV I ever had, but maybe the
best, was on

39:53.358 --> 39:54.525 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
"Meet the Press."

39:54.559 --> 39:57.362 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I did a show sometimes called
"Imus in the
Morning."

39:57.395 --> 40:00.698 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Tim Russert did that show
and David Gregory.

40:00.732 --> 40:02.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And he said some racist things.

40:02.467 --> 40:05.837 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I didn't realize he had
already said some
racist things about her.

40:05.870 --> 40:08.539 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And she was on the show, and she
just was
super tough on us.

40:08.573 --> 40:09.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

40:09.574 --> 40:10.541 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I remember that.

40:10.575 --> 40:12.377 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: But then the
intense warmth.

40:12.410 --> 40:16.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have a photo on my phone of
you and Gwen
doing an exploding fist bump at
the convention.

40:16.981 --> 40:21.119 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And she's laughing and she's
dancing in her
chair, that warmth, that smile.

40:21.152 --> 40:22.887 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And the two were so in tandem.

40:22.920 --> 40:27.759 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, our mutual
friend John
Dickerson over at CBS said you
could read

40:27.792 --> 40:29.494 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a book by the light of her
smile.

40:29.527 --> 40:31.896 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think we all agree with
that.

40:31.929 --> 40:35.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ruth Marcus, David Brooks, we
thank you.

40:35.266 --> 40:40.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, with that, before we go
tonight, we wanted
to let members of our own
"NewsHour" family,

40:40.905 --> 40:45.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
past and present, on camera and
behind the
camera, pay tribute to Gwen.

40:45.943 --> 40:48.913 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As you know, she passed away
earlier this
week.

40:48.946 --> 40:52.183 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She will be remembered at
services this weekend
here in Washington.

40:52.216 --> 40:57.021 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Personally, I'm the luckiest
person I know
because I had the privilege of
being Gwen

40:57.055 --> 41:07.498 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ifill's friend and her sidekick
at work.

41:07.532 --> 41:09.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She was like a magnet.

41:09.400 --> 41:13.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People just wanted to be close
to her because
she instinctively cared about
how they were

41:13.705 --> 41:14.872 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
doing.

41:14.906 --> 41:15.873 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We joked.

41:15.907 --> 41:17.675 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We were like an old married
couple.

41:17.709 --> 41:21.579 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We weren't afraid to say the
really important
stuff to each other's faces,
like, you have

41:21.612 --> 41:27.652 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
got salad in your teeth, or,
where did you
find those fabulous earrings?

41:27.685 --> 41:32.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As a work partner, she was the
ultimate, holding
me and everyone else here at the
"NewsHour"

41:32.857 --> 41:35.026 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to the highest standards.

41:35.059 --> 41:37.161 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Her mantra was, "Assume
nothing."

41:37.195 --> 41:38.863 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
"How do you know?"

41:38.896 --> 41:41.232 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I can hear her asking.

41:41.265 --> 41:43.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Boy, do we miss her.

41:43.201 --> 41:45.536 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There is an empty place in our
hearts.

41:45.570 --> 41:52.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we will carry on, as Gwen
would want,
with a commitment to being
thorough, being

41:52.076 --> 41:58.916 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fair and to shedding light,
rather than heat,
on everything we cover.

41:58.950 --> 42:06.491 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TRAVIS DAUB: What I learned from
Gwen as a
journalist is to never accept
the easy answer.

42:06.524 --> 42:08.526 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There is often another layer to
a problem.

42:08.559 --> 42:13.564 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
There is often another
motivation driving
someone behind an issue.

42:13.598 --> 42:15.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it's our job to find out
what that is.

42:15.500 --> 42:19.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNY MARDER: For every story,
you need to
think about, what is the
question that's important

42:19.604 --> 42:21.439 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to ask and why does it matter?

42:21.472 --> 42:26.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSHUA BARAJAS: No matter how
complicated
and how fraught the
conversations I have with

42:26.244 --> 42:29.013 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people, Gwen taught me how to
listen.

42:29.046 --> 42:38.523 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: There is a
professional
ladder in this business, but, as
a journalist

42:38.556 --> 42:43.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of color, what she impressed
upon me, as a
friend and a mentor, is that
it's not just

42:43.661 --> 42:46.230 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
enough to climb that ladder.

42:46.264 --> 42:51.536 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's about making sure that you
pull someone
else up, and then they pull
someone else up

42:51.569 --> 42:53.337 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
along the way.

42:53.371 --> 42:57.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JASMINE WRIGHT: It's no longer
an exception
to see a black woman who looks
just like me

42:57.408 --> 43:02.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
anchoring the nightly news,
reporting on foreign
policy and politics, but that
it's the norm.

43:02.213 --> 43:06.184 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AMANDA GOMEZ: Race and gender
doesn't define
my reporting.

43:06.217 --> 43:07.418 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It adds to it.

43:07.452 --> 43:09.287 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It strengthens it.

43:09.320 --> 43:12.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KAMARIA ROBERTS: Determined and
focused, despite
what naysayers may have to say
about you and

43:12.857 --> 43:13.825 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
your work.

43:13.858 --> 43:15.660 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
WOMAN: Believe in wonder.

43:15.693 --> 43:17.295 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She taught me to be bold.

43:17.328 --> 43:19.797 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She taught me that black women
are magical.

43:19.831 --> 43:27.371 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JIM LEHRER: We heard that there
was an opportunity
for her to come possibly to PBS
to do "Washington

43:27.405 --> 43:33.144 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Week," but even possibly be a
correspondent
on the "NewsHour."

43:33.177 --> 43:38.883 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Linda Winslow, who was then the
executive
producer of the "NewsHour," and
I had dinner

43:38.916 --> 43:43.087 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with Gwen, and we talked about
her coming
aboard as a correspondent.

43:43.120 --> 43:46.791 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And almost right there, she
accepted.

43:46.824 --> 43:50.595 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And to our new senior
correspondent, Gwen
Ifill, welcome, Gwen.

43:50.628 --> 43:52.129 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Thanks, Jim.

43:52.163 --> 43:56.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JIM LEHRER: And there she was,
one of us.

43:56.167 --> 44:03.741 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was a superb professional,
somebody who
understood the need to be civil,
understand

44:03.774 --> 44:14.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the need to be honest, the need
to do your
homework, and the need to be
tough when required,

44:14.852 --> 44:23.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to be soft when required, and
more importantly,
always to be yourself, which
Gwen always was.

44:24.028 --> 44:30.735 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAR SILVER: Gwen Ifill was a
class act.

44:30.768 --> 44:36.307 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Everybody who spent any time
with her, both
professionally and outside the
studio, was

44:36.340 --> 44:39.777 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
aware of the fact that she was a
consummate
professional.

44:39.810 --> 44:44.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAM KIRKLAND: Gwen taught me to
keep digging,
that, even when I thought all
the questions

44:44.649 --> 44:48.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
had been answered in a story,
that there were
always more questions to ask.

44:48.185 --> 44:50.021 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LEAH NAGY: To always ask, so
what?

44:50.054 --> 44:52.323 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How does the story affect people
across the
country?

44:52.356 --> 44:54.125 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Why should they care?

44:54.158 --> 44:57.495 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOE BUCKINGHAM: Was to always
remember the
importance of words, the right
words at the

44:57.528 --> 44:59.263 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
right time.

44:59.297 --> 45:03.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: We shared a
journalist's
passion for explaining to our
audience how

45:03.601 --> 45:08.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the world works, but with
honesty and care,
not cynicism.

45:08.139 --> 45:13.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Most precious of all was her
wise counsel,
reminding me in tough times to
rely on family,

45:13.711 --> 45:14.812 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
friends and faith.

45:14.845 --> 45:17.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They were the greatest source of
Gwen's gusto
and joy.

45:17.982 --> 45:24.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Gwen taught me, in
the more than
30 years we knew each other, the
value and

45:24.155 --> 45:25.489 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the power of friendship.

45:25.523 --> 45:27.625 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAN COONEY: What did I learn
from Gwen?

45:27.658 --> 45:31.662 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
She reinforced in me the
difference a smile
can make in someone's day.

45:31.696 --> 45:37.001 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MIKE MELIA: Kindness and
curiosity are the
best tools that we have to love
and to live.

45:37.034 --> 45:40.938 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JIM SCHNEIDER: Live with
integrity and grace
all the time.

45:40.972 --> 45:47.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LINDA WINSLOW: When her strong,
compassionate
heart stopped beating on Monday,
those of

45:47.244 --> 45:55.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
us who knew and loved her, her
friends and
her colleagues and the audience
as well, knew

45:55.286 --> 45:58.990 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that our own hearts had taken a
direct hit.

45:59.023 --> 46:00.424 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She was our inspiration.

46:00.458 --> 46:05.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She was the person who told us
that the work
we did really mattered.

46:05.630 --> 46:13.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was a stickler for accuracy,
and she was
also a fun-loving,
life-affirming, deeply

46:13.838 --> 46:16.907 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
religious friend.

46:16.941 --> 46:21.412 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I'm going to miss her very
much.

46:21.445 --> 46:29.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALEXIS COX: Gwen taught me that,
as a woman
in a challenging profession, I
have a responsibility

46:29.387 --> 46:31.622 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to help other women succeed.

46:31.656 --> 46:35.359 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She also taught me to never
underestimate
the power of a great statement
necklace.

46:35.393 --> 46:38.029 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MEREDITH GARRETSON: That leopard
print is
business casual.

46:38.062 --> 46:42.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAN SAGALYN: She always said, "I
like your
haircut," whenever I got a
haircut, and that

46:42.400 --> 46:44.268 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
hair was really important.

46:44.301 --> 46:50.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLIE IDE: I learned a lot
from Gwen professionally
and personally, but I also
learned how to

46:50.875 --> 46:52.576 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
let off some steam.

46:52.610 --> 46:57.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the best way to do it is to
give a good
uppercut to Bozo.

46:57.581 --> 47:00.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GLYNDA BATES: Gwen taught me
never to call
her Gwennie.

47:01.018 --> 47:05.589 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT MACNEIL: Many years ago,
at the dawn
of television, some radio
comedian said, it's

47:05.623 --> 47:07.858 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
easy to make it on TV.

47:07.892 --> 47:09.460 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All you have to do is fake
